# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets: response headers (copied to dist/ by Vite).
#
# Goal: new deploys reach users without a hard refresh.
#  - The HTML shell (/, SPA routes, /index.html) and the service worker
#    (/sw.js, /registerSW.js, /workbox-*.js) must be REVALIDATED on every load
#    (no-cache), so the browser always sees the newest bundle references and
#    detects a new service worker.
#  - The content-hashed bundles under /assets/ never change for a given URL, so
#    they're cached hard (immutable). A new deploy emits new hashed filenames.
#
# Later, more-specific rules win, so /assets/* overrides the /* no-cache below.

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
